## Summary - Mobile Text Readability Fix

**Problem**: Grey text in AXION response area was hard to read on mobile (circled in your screenshot).

**Solution**: Added mobile-specific CSS overrides in the `@media (max-width: 768px)` section:

```css
/* Mobile: Make AXION response text white and larger for readability */
.response-area {
    font-size: 16px !important;
    line-height: 1.6 !important;
    color: var(--text) !important;
}
.response-area .message-assistant,
.response-area .message-user {
    color: var(--text) !important;
    font-size: 16px !important;
}
.live-activity-content {
    color: var(--text) !important;
    font-size: 15px !important;
    line-height: 1.6 !important;
}
.streaming-progress .message-assistant {
    color: var(--text) !important;
}
```

**Changes**:
- Changed text color from `--text-secondary` (grey) to `--text` (white) on mobile
- Increased font size from 12-15px to 16px for better readability
- Increased line height to 1.6 for better spacing

**Screenshot**: `/opt/clawd/projects/relay/.screenshots/mobile_axion_text_after.png` shows the improved white text.

